.SH NAME
\fBhklscan\fP \- general linear scan in reciprocal space
.\" spec reStructuredText documentation
.
\fP
.PP
.\" @(#)hklscan.rst      6.1  08/01/12  CSS
.
.\" Copyright (c) 1990,1991,1995,2012 Certified Scientific Software
.
.\" 
.
.\" versioninfo: "hklscan" "macro" "08/01/12" "hklscan.rst 6.1  08/01/12 CSS"
.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.rs
.sp
\fBhklscan Hstart Hend Kstart Kend Lstart Lend intervals time\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.rs
.sp
\fBhklscan\fP is a linear scan in reciprocal space over the three coordinates
\fBH K L\fP which range from \fBHstart\fP, \fBKstart\fP and
\fBLstart\fP to \fBHend\fP, \fBKend\fP and
\fBLend\fP, respectively.  The step size for each coordinate is
(\fBstart \- end)/intervals\fP.  The number of data points collected will be
\fBintervals+1\fP.
Count time is given by \fBtime\fP, which if positive,
specifies seconds and if negative,
specifies monitor counts.
.SH "EXAMPLE"
.rs
.sp
\fBhklscan .9 1.1 .9 1.1 0 0 10 10\fP
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.rs
.sp
